    {
      "id": "RQ-0014",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Redact public-readiness secret scan findings",
      "description": "Principles violated: I) Security baseline, F) Fail fast appropriately, H) Operational hygiene. The public-readiness scanner detects high-confidence secrets but prints the exact matched secret with match.group(0). That can leak credentials into terminal logs, release evidence, copied reports, or CI transcripts. Minimal fix: replace raw match output with a redacted finding format that still identifies file, line, and pattern type, and update tests so injected tokens are detected but never echoed.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "security",
        "release"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "scripts/lib/public_readiness_scan.py",
        "crates/ralph/tests/release_integration_contract_test.rs",
        "scripts/pre-public-check.sh"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: scripts/lib/public_readiness_scan.py:241 :: scan_secrets appends match.group(0) directly to each problem line.",
        "path: crates/ralph/tests/release_integration_contract_test.rs:2836 :: existing test coverage explicitly expects the scanner output to contain the full injected token.",
        "workflow: python3 scripts/lib/public_readiness_scan.py secrets <temp repo with a fake GitHub token> :: status=1 and stdout printed README.md:1: github_classic_token followed by the raw token value.",
        "path: AGENTS.md:288 :: repository guidance says to never print secrets."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add a helper that renders secret matches as redacted metadata, for example pattern name plus length or short digest, without including the matched value.",
        "Update the secret-scan tests to assert the scanner reports the file, line, and pattern while stdout/stderr do not contain the injected token or private-key body.",
        "Run the focused proof command with a disposable fake token and confirm the scan still exits nonzero without echoing the token.",
        "Verify by running cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop --test release_integration_contract_test public_readiness and make check-env-safety."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: Simplify code while preserving nuanced runner behavior",
      "created_at": "2026-04-17T23:11:06Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-17T23:11:06Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "scan_agent": "scan-maintenance"
      }
