      "id": "RQ-0020",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Make built-in profile behavior visible in CLI and docs",
      "description": "Principles violated: G) Least astonishment, J) Consistency/Integrity. The CLI lists built-in profiles safe and power-user as no overrides even though they change approval and git publish behavior. The profiles feature doc also says profiles are not built in and uses stale config version 1 examples. Minimal fix: update profile summaries to include safety/publish overrides and align docs with the built-in profile contract.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "profiles",
        "docs",
        "cli"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/config.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/profiles.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/agent/profiles.rs",
        "docs/features/profiles.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "workflow: ralph config profiles list :: output was Available profiles: power-user - no overrides; safe - no overrides.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/cli/config.rs:136 :: format_profile_summary only summarizes runner, model, phases, and reasoning_effort.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/profiles.rs:27 :: power-user sets claude_permission_mode bypass, approval_mode yolo, and git_publish_mode commit_and_push.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/profiles.rs:42 :: safe sets claude_permission_mode accept-edits, approval_mode safe, and git_publish_mode off.",
        "path: docs/features/profiles.md:18 :: docs say profiles are not built in.",
        "path: docs/features/profiles.md:24 :: docs use config version 1.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/agent/profiles.rs:46 :: tests assert built-in safe and power-user profiles are listed."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Extend format_profile_summary to include approval_mode, claude_permission_mode, and git_publish_mode in concise list output.",
        "Add focused tests for built-in profile summaries so safety-sensitive overrides cannot disappear from the CLI again.",
        "Update docs/features/profiles.md to say safe and power-user are built in, user profiles are additive, reserved names cannot be redefined, and examples use version 2.",
        "Verify by running ralph config profiles list and confirming safe and power-user display their safety/publish behavior."
      ],
      "notes": [],
