    {
      "id": "RQ-0022",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Refuse lossy legacy CI gate shell-string migration",
      "description": "Principles violated: F) Fail fast appropriately, G) Least astonishment, J) Consistency/Integrity. CI gate execution is argv-only and shell launchers are rejected, but the legacy migration shlex-splits old shell command strings. A legacy command like cargo test && cargo clippy becomes argv that runs cargo with literal && arguments instead of preserving shell semantics. Minimal fix: detect shell metacharacters or multi-command legacy strings during migration and fail with guidance to use a checked-in script or explicit argv.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "config",
        "migration",
        "ci"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/migration/config_migrations/ci_gate.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/config/validation/ci_gate.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/migration/config_migrations/tests.rs",
        "docs/features/supervision.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/migration/config_migrations/ci_gate.rs:17 :: module invariant says enabled legacy shell strings are migrated to argv-only execution via shlex::split.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/migration/config_migrations/ci_gate.rs:82 :: build_ci_gate_value calls shlex::split(command).",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/config/validation/ci_gate.rs:40 :: validation rejects shell launchers such as sh -c but does not reject literal shell metacharacters passed to a non-shell program.",
        "workflow: rg -n \"build_ci_gate_value|ci_gate_command|shlex|shell launcher\" crates/ralph/src/migration/config_migrations crates/ralph/src/config/validation :: found no test coverage for legacy compound commands using &&, pipes, or redirects."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add migration validation for legacy ci_gate_command strings that contain shell control operators such as &&, ||, ;, |, or redirects.",
        "For unsupported shell strings, return an actionable migration error that points users to a checked-in script and argv form.",
        "Keep simple legacy commands like make ci migrating to [\"make\", \"ci\"].",
        "Update supervision docs so compound CI examples use script wrappers instead of shell strings.",
        "Verify with migration tests for simple commands, disabled gates, and rejected compound shell strings."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: Simplify code while preserving nuanced runner behavior",
