      "id": "RQ-0023",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Capture multi-word runner subcommand help",
      "description": "Principles violated: C) DRY knowledge, H) Operational hygiene, J) Consistency/Integrity. runner_cli_inventory.sh is intended to preserve nuanced runner CLI behavior, but it parses and invokes only single-token subcommands. Multi-word surfaces such as exec resume are dropped, which weakens the inventory exactly where session-resume behavior is runner-specific. Minimal fix: represent discovered commands as argv arrays plus filesystem-safe labels and capture help for multi-word commands.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "runner",
        "tooling"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "scripts/runner_cli_inventory.sh",
        "crates/ralph/tests/runner_cli_inventory_script_test.rs"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: scripts/runner_cli_inventory.sh:319 :: parser captures only one command token from tool command style help lines.",
        "path: scripts/runner_cli_inventory.sh:324 :: standard-format parser also captures only a single command token.",
        "path: scripts/runner_cli_inventory.sh:377 :: help capture invokes only \"$bin\" \"$subcmd\" \"--help\".",
        "path: crates/ralph/tests/runner_cli_inventory_script_test.rs:37 :: test fixture includes exec resume Resume a previous session.",
        "path: crates/ralph/tests/runner_cli_inventory_script_test.rs:137 :: test asserts help.exec.txt only, not help.exec.resume.txt.",
        "workflow: disposable fake runner with exec and exec resume help; run scripts/runner_cli_inventory.sh --out <tmp> :: captured help.exec.txt only and logged captured 1 subcommand(s)."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Change runner inventory discovery to store subcommands as argv arrays and generate safe file labels such as help.exec.resume.txt.",
        "Invoke multi-word help as \"$bin\" exec resume --help while preserving single-token behavior.",
        "Update consolidated markdown output to include multi-word subcommands.",
        "Add a regression test using the existing exec resume fixture and assert help.exec.resume.txt is created.",
        "Verify by running cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop --test runner_cli_inventory_script_test."
      ],
      "notes": [],
